## For serious portfolio use

Add **movement significance**:

```python
df["impact_score"] = abs(df["day_change_pct"]) * df["portfolio_weight"]
```

Where:

```python
df["portfolio_weight"] = df["current_value"] / df["current_value"].sum()
```

This tells you:

> which stock movement actually matters to your portfolio.

Example:

| Stock         | Day % | Weight | Impact Score |
| ------------- | ----: | -----: | -----------: |
| Small holding |   +5% |     1% |         0.05 |
| Large holding | +1.5% |    20% |         0.30 |

The second one matters more.

